1
00:00:13,460 --> 00:00:21,960
Ladies and gentlemen, welcome to the Ethereum Application Gathering hosted by Ethereum Application Guild, aka EAG,

2
00:00:21,960 --> 00:00:32,960
a global non-profit collaborative organization dedicated to advancing the innovation, adoption, and real-world impact of the Ethereum native applications.

3
00:00:32,960 --> 00:00:36,960
I'm today's MC Yu Yan, and I'll be with you all day.

4
00:00:37,460 --> 00:00:45,460
The Ethereum infrastructure has reached a new level of maturity, and the focus is increasingly shifting towards applications.

5
00:00:45,460 --> 00:00:58,460
Today, we will have a four-chapter discussion towards where momentum is forming, what challenges remain, and how applications are beginning to take shape in practice.

6
00:00:58,460 --> 00:01:05,460
Let's start with Chapter 1, From Infrastructure to Applications, Ethereum's Next Phase.

7
00:01:05,960 --> 00:01:17,960
We will have an overview of the latest developments across Ethereum, its key infrastructure layers, and how these advances are shaping readiness for real-world applications.

8
00:01:17,960 --> 00:01:28,960
Our first chapter will kick off with an inspiring opening speech by Dr. Xiao Feng, Chairman of Wan Xiang Blockchain, Chairman and CEO of Hashkey Group.

9
00:01:29,460 --> 00:01:37,460
Please welcome the Chairman of Wan Xiang Blockchain, Chairman and CEO of Hashkey Group, Dr. Xiao Feng, to give us his opening speech. Please welcome.

10
00:01:54,180 --> 00:02:04,180
Good morning, everyone. Welcome to the Ethereum Application Gathering hosted by EAG.

11
00:02:04,680 --> 00:02:13,680
The Ethereum Application Gathering, EAG, originated in 2014.

12
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:19,680
In 2014, I made a judgment, which I later shared with many of my friends,

13
00:02:19,680 --> 00:02:27,680
that blockchain technology has entered the Internet's 1950s.

14
00:02:28,180 --> 00:02:36,180
That is to say, blockchain technology has developed enough to support large-scale commercial applications.

15
00:02:36,180 --> 00:02:44,180
We know that most of the Internet platforms, we are now familiar with the Internet platforms,

16
00:02:44,180 --> 00:02:53,180
were actually born between 1995 and 2005.

17
00:02:53,680 --> 00:03:01,680
In addition to Amazon, which was founded in 1994, most of the applications were created in the 1950s.

18
00:03:01,680 --> 00:03:09,680
So the real large-scale applications of the Internet started in 1995.

19
00:03:11,680 --> 00:03:16,680
There are several conditions for the emergence of the Internet in 1995.

20
00:03:17,180 --> 00:03:26,180
First of all, if the computer's control system, operating system, is still DAO,

21
00:03:26,180 --> 00:03:32,180
and if it interacts with the computer by command line,

22
00:03:32,180 --> 00:03:36,180
I believe there will not be a big outbreak of Internet applications.

23
00:03:37,180 --> 00:03:42,180
Later, from the DAO browser, there was a dialogue box,

24
00:03:42,180 --> 00:03:45,180
and then developed a graphics operating system.

25
00:03:45,680 --> 00:03:48,680
The graphics operating system is like Windows.

26
00:03:48,680 --> 00:03:56,680
It allows more people to interact with computers in a more convenient way.

27
00:03:57,680 --> 00:04:01,680
With this condition, with the development of technology,

28
00:04:01,680 --> 00:04:04,680
Internet applications have only just begun to appear.

29
00:04:04,680 --> 00:04:07,680
Of course, there are other conditions, including bandwidth,

30
00:04:07,680 --> 00:04:10,680
a construction of communication facilities.

31
00:04:11,180 --> 00:04:15,180
So the reason why I say that since 2004,

32
00:04:15,180 --> 00:04:20,180
the blockchain has also entered a time when such an application broke out

33
00:04:20,180 --> 00:04:25,180
is because at that time, many technologies of the blockchain,

34
00:04:25,180 --> 00:04:34,180
some application tools, some mechanisms and means of construction of infrastructure,

35
00:04:34,680 --> 00:04:41,680
have also begun to be able to use some commercial applications.

36
00:04:41,680 --> 00:04:43,680
So I made such a judgment at that time.

37
00:04:43,680 --> 00:04:47,680
So, of course, in addition to this judgment,

38
00:04:47,680 --> 00:04:53,680
we also continue to discuss with people in the entire ecosystem

39
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:56,680
and people with application scenarios

40
00:04:56,680 --> 00:05:03,680
how to establish such a commercial application on the blockchain.

41
00:05:04,680 --> 00:05:09,680
So last year, in the second half of the year,

42
00:05:09,680 --> 00:05:17,680
in Singapore, we launched the ETAFORM application alliance, EAG.

43
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:21,680
The ETAFORM's title, this abbreviation,

44
00:05:21,680 --> 00:05:26,680
is because we discussed with the founder of ETAFORM, Vitalik,

45
00:05:26,680 --> 00:05:29,680
what kind of abbreviation would be better?

46
00:05:30,180 --> 00:05:37,180
In fact, Vitalik should be the name for this name.

47
00:05:37,180 --> 00:05:41,180
Vitalik is of course very supportive of us

48
00:05:41,180 --> 00:05:45,180
to launch such a global application alliance.

49
00:05:45,180 --> 00:05:50,650
So another background of EAG's establishment

50
00:05:50,650 --> 00:05:55,650
is that we have had a community activity in ETAFORM

51
00:05:55,650 --> 00:06:02,820
called the Three Seas House since 2024 and 2025.

52
00:06:02,820 --> 00:06:08,320
The Three Seas House was in Singapore last year in 2025.

53
00:06:08,320 --> 00:06:12,320
There were dozens of global developers

54
00:06:12,320 --> 00:06:19,320
